values:
Hello all,
Long time no post. I really hope I didn't start my last entry like that. Well lots of stuff has been going on. For starters I got my boy still. Since 10/13/2004. Still happily dating a Canadian. He is actually en route to here now. Yeah! Still doing the RA thing. Haven't jumped in a while, bullsh!t. School is caring on as usual. Lame! My house got broken into by some assh*les and if I ever find them they are freaking dead. Living on campus is great, I really missed it. My apartment mates are great. If only we could bomb our next door neighbors who at this exact time are yelling about something. Besides that all is well. My sister is getting remarried in May to her boyfriend Al. Which should be fun. Picking out dresses on sunday. Soo that is all. I hope that all is well for everyone else. Bye 4 Now
Blue Skies
~T

Yeah...
Soo this will have to be quick because my obnoxious dog is whinny because she is freaking retarded. Not much going on. Lifeguading, Skydiving, the usual. I broke my laptop soo I can't go on the internet anywhere else, but where my dog sleeps and I want to kill her. And that is all I can say before I through her out the window. I will have to try to update later.
Blue Skies

Ahhh......Live Journal. It hasn't been too long. I started lifeguarding and it has been cool. I spent 5 hours in the blazing heat today, which was ok I suppose. I loved when all the kids left soo I could swim and go down the slide. The slide is sweet! It is covered and spiral. Good Times! Today I got to hang out with my on again off again friend Melissa. She is now living with her gf in Melrose, really close to my house. I still haven't met her girl yet, but she seems really cool. She even went to SSC! GO VIKINGS!! enough of that. I went and saw Harry Potter on the opening day, because I am a geek. I liked it even though it was missing crucial parts from the book. Still good though. Tommorrow I get to lifeguard a canoeing classs, which should be interesting and then I am going skydiving for the weekend. Next week starts the camps at the YMCA which means I start my 20 hours a week. Yeah Money!! Primus is playing at the Pavillion on Wednesday tix are $40 , but I don't know anyone who would go. Damn me and my lack of friends. We got a hot tub and are in the process of setting up everything soo it will work. Fun Fun!! and with having said that my mom is going away for the first weekend in July and I don't have drill!! Soo a possible party is in the makings. Who knows though. Skydiving might be a better idea. We shall see. That is about all I have now, soo I will update when more happens. Ohh one last thing... I dyed my hair normal brown and then a wine/red over it. I think it looks cool. I liked being blonde but being a lifeuard I was getting much too tan to be a blonde and it started getting green from the chlorine. Ok now really that is it.
Blue Skies
Twiggy

I just got home today, I have been at Skydive New England since May 13. Lots of good times, even though I only jumped 20 times. Lots of good times. Lots and Lots. Hung out with many cool people and only slept in my tent 5 times alone. Go me!! Over cute Tandem instructor of last season, mainly so I can focus on new Aussie Tandem Instructor. One word. DREDS!! Yep dreds! Ahhh! Did lots of stuff, like went on a motorcycle, and a 4 wheeler,got to drive the SNE van, went to a bar marketing SNE, played pool with 2 very very hot men, got hit on a lot, met cool people some from Vermont and some from Haverhill, Saw my Aunt Kay, had my first cutaway!!, and the list continues it has been a fun time, but unfortunately I am home now. Ick! I start working at SSC on Wednesday and then the Y after that. We will see how that goes, but for now I am tired. Too much partying the last 2 weeks need some serious sleep! Just wanted to give a great big congratulations to my X roomate Becky for Graduating!! Yeah Becky!! You Rock.
Twiggy

Well I guess this is my monthly update. I tend to only update once a month, I suck. Well starting in August I will be back to updating constantly, once I move on campus. Last couple of days I have been hanging out at school. There was the big horseshoe party on Wednesday and I decided to go. I got really drunk and smoked a little. It was just a really interesting concept to be able to walk around the horeshoe and just drink infront of the campus police. It was pretty fun and there was about 600 people there. Completely different than FSC. Then I went to my school's 150th Bday party they were giving out great prizes like laptops, digital cameras, TV's and stuff like that. I won the new No Doubt CD. Wow! Well the party was fun though. We also had a SAAC, (student athletes something something)  meeting and an RA(Resident Assistant) meeting. I slept over TB's place. The SAAC meeting was fun free food. It is odd though they are like " You might walk past an athlete in the hall and not even know" I was thinking would I really care if I saw an athlete and how would I feel if someone was like "you are an athlete" to me. It's not like I don't want people to know, but I don't want to be percieved as a Jock. The RA stuff is crazy we are going on an overnight trip to an island and doing some team builder or something. Crazy stuff. I also move in an entire month before everyone else does. Argh! Can't wait till my finals are done. I have 2 left. Then I go skydiving for 2 weeks striaght if anyone wants to visit me give me a call and go here for directions http://www.skydivene.com/jDirections.html#anchor lebanon
I leave next thursday and won't be back until June 1st. My cellphone sometimes works, take the chance and call first. Bit for now that is all.

Soo, its been a while let me catch you up: Still not really with Jay, got my Lifeguard certification, still doing the school thing, Got and RA position in the 21+ drinking dorm in the fall, and the Drop Zone opened a couple of weeks ago. Ok caught up?? Soo went and saw Kill Bill volume 2 with Sherina on Friday, realy good movie. Can't wait till its relleased it will be cool to watch them together. Saturday woke up and went to the DropZone. Got there around noon and the first load still didn't go up crazy? Well the plane was having issues, shortly later the plane was good. Couldn't find anyone that was free to do a refresher jump with me, soo just cholled and met a chick named Jenny who goes to Monserat in Beverly, she was pretty cool she couldn't jump, because she was AFF and they were on a wind hold. Soo watching people jump, 2 cutaways, including 1 off a tandem, then the last jump 7 people landed off. 5 in trees, 1 on a road 8 miles away and 1 in some power lines. Everyone was fine, but they were in the front page of teh sunday paper in Maine. Then Saturday night took some pills, and shrooms and drank. Needless to say it was a good time. Stayed up really late like 4 or 5 am then got up at 8am to jump. Eveyone was draggin ass. I was just sitting there chilling and Mikey came over and was like ok you and me are on the 2nd load. Let me recap. Last season I had such a crush on Mikey and the first jump I did with him I was retarded and couldn't get off the plane, how freaking embarrassing. Well yesterday, I was nervous and we jumped and everything was going fine, then I docked him and he leaned over and kissed me. Inflight kiss. How feaking cool was that. I think I was a little shocked at the time. We fell forever it felt and he actually had to check my altimeter because he thought that his was broken. I thought it was pretty freaking funny. Landed fine but away from the "P". Second jump of the day was supposed to be a 2 way but it didn't happen. Landed again far from the "P". Last jump had a pretty successful 2 way and landed on the "P". Yeah!! I am soo glad to be jumping again. I feel soo much better and centered again. I can breathe!! That was lame but whatever. Sunday's party was pretty lame, but I hung out and talked to Greg MacBeth, who is pretty dam cool and wo has 2 very successful skydiving sons. He was a pretty cool, down to earth guy. He owns a DZ in Canada, so if I ever go to Canda I will probably check it out. And really that is all from this weekend. I did the first half of the Professional CPR and First Aid class I need to do for Lifeguarding and then I am done, but I have 3 tests this week. including Math, Music and Anatomy. Its going to be a stressful week and then I go and visit my Aunt Kay for the weekend. Can't jump for 3 weeks. I have drill the following week after Aunt Kay's. I think when school is all over with I am going to go to the DZ for a week or 2 at a time. I think that would be freaking cool. I will have to stock up on food first though, or I will be poor. Well should be getting ready for school and such. It will be good to sleep in a bed tonight. I will hopefully update soon, but you never know with me.
Twiggy

We got our puppy on saturday. She is soo cute, but she keeps peeing and crapping all over the place. Went to Framingham and then to Hampden to go to Becky's party with Tony. Good times. Evil Nick is really hot! Went home and did the stupid sychronized swimming paper, which is due tomorrow. Got my math test back, I got a 90 could have easily gotten 100, but I screwed up the sign. Hopefully will get back my music test. I have to do my presentation tomorrow, as well as finally disect the piggy pig. I also have to bring Shadow and Morgan to the vet tomorrow. I went up to Skydive New England today and got my jumpsuit I will probably have a picture of it soon. I also gave them $700 soo I have a block of 100 jumps on my account for next season. I want to have at least 200 jumps by the fall, we will see. Jay is coming down tomorrow, which is cool I haven't seen him in a while. We have drill this weekend and we are going to see the Vagina Monologues on Saturday with Sherina so that should be  fun. Then a music test on friday. Busy Busy. I can't wait till Spring Break even though I am not going to be doing much, but there is no work that I really need to do. After I get back to school after Spring Break I find out about the RA position. I am really nervous about that.
